"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The function datestr2num expects a single date string as input, not a list. The code incorrectly passes a list comprehension to it, which will raise a TypeError. Instead, the dates should be converted individually before being passed to datestr2num.\", \"patch\": \"9c9\\n< x = datestr2num([datetime.strptime(day, '%d/%m/%Y').strftime('%m/%d/%Y') for day in days])\\n---\\n> x = [datestr2num(datetime.strptime(day, '%d/%m/%Y').strftime('%m/%d/%Y')) for day in days]\"}"